						<summary>

						<p>This records a gift of 96 sheep for a perpetual lamp in the temple of Tiruviśalūr Perumāṉaḍigaḷ by Pāgaṉ Sarvadēvaṉ the headman of Kiḷinallūr in Kiḻār-kūṟṟam. The Sanskrit portion at the beginning makes mention the gift of a gold fillet to the god by the same donor.</p>						

						</summary>
